PHOTOS: SuppliedSAPS officers and Port Shepstone Primary pupils. Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories PORT Shepstone SAPS conducted a crime awareness campaign during Child Protection Week and visited various schools to talk to pupils. Some of the schools visited were Marburg Primary, Umalusi Primary in Mehlomnyama, Port Shepstone Islamic School, Merlewood Secondary and Port Shepstone Primary. The police officers spoke to pupils about bullying, road safety, carrying of dangerous weapons, child abuse and stranger danger. Supplied.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.